name: Abandoned House #3
description:
The 3rd piece in my "Well-Worn Places" series, and the final variation of this house. This burned out, abandoned house sat in a small barren wood in Louisville, KY. It was torn down shortly after this photo was taken.

The 1st image of this house was toned brown, to suggest it was rejoining nature as it decayed, the 2nd was toned green, to evoke an uneasy sense of sickness in the structure, and this 3rd I left b&w, lending it an ominous presence even from afar.

35 mm film, circa 2001.
